article.headline: The Citadel 78, Cincinnati Christian 55
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Cameron Wells scored 20 points to lead The Citadel Bulldogs to a 78-55 win over Cincinnati Christian on Saturday night. Wells shot 8-for-13 from the field, helping the Bulldogs (2-2) end a two-game losing streak. Demetrius Nelson added 17 points and four rebounds for Citadel. Nathanael Harney scored 12 points for the Eagles (4-2). Harney shot 5-for-9 from the field and grabbed four rebounds. The Bulldogs shot 47.1 percent from the field (24-for-51), and attempted 31 free-throws as a team, converting 23 of their attempts (74.2 percent). They also managed to block five shots -- two of which were made by Nelson.
